President Obama has announced his intention to nominate Cathy Russell for the position of Ambassador at Large for Global Women’s Issues at the Department of State. Russell has a long history of advocating for justice and fairness, particularly in relation to preventing violence against women. She has previously served as Chief of Staff to Dr. Jill Biden and as the Senior Advisor on International Women’s Issues on the Senate Foreign Relations Committee. Russell's experience also includes working in the Justice Department and serving as Staff Director of the Senate Judiciary Committee. She has a B.A. from Boston College and a J.D. from George Washington University.